import pandas as pd
import seaborn as sns
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    
    source_counts = data['source'].value_counts()
    target_counts = data['target'].value_counts()
    
    ax1 = sns.barplot(x=source_counts.index, y=source_counts.values, color='blue', alpha=0.5, label='Source')
    ax2 = sns.barplot(x=target_counts.index, y=target_counts.values, color='red', alpha=0.5, label='Target')
    
    plt.xlabel('Categories')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.legend(loc='upper right')
    
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    plt.title('What is the distribution of source and target in the dataset?', wrap=True)
    
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()

import seaborn as sns
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    source_target_counts = data.groupby(['source', 'target']).size().unstack(fill_value=0)
    sns.heatmap(source_target_counts, annot=True, fmt="d", cmap="YlGnBu")
    plt.title("What is the most common source and target combination in the dataset?", wrap=True)
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()

import seaborn as sns
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    avg_targets_per_source = data.groupby('source')['target'].count().mean()
    sns.barplot(x='source', y='target', data=data, estimator=len, ci=None)
    plt.axhline(avg_targets_per_source, color='red', linestyle='--', label=f'Average: {avg_targets_per_source:.2f}')
    plt.legend()
    plt.title('What is the average number of targets per source in the dataset?', wrap=True)
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()

import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    unique_counts = data['source'].append(data['target']).value_counts()
    plt.pie(unique_counts, labels=unique_counts.index, autopct='%1.1f%%')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of unique sources and targets in the dataset?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
